President Obama has declared a major disaster in Pennsylvania due to severe winter storms and snowstorms that occurred from February 5-11, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement the Commonwealth and local recovery efforts. Federal funding is available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and emergency protective measures in various counties. Hazard mitigation measures are also eligible for federal funding. Regis Leo Phelan has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further information can be obtained from FEMA.